    <div class="occlss-layout__col occlss-layout__col--12">
      <div class="occlss-layout example-section">
        <div class="occlss-layout__col occlss-layout__col--sm-7">
          <p>
            There are some nuances with flexbox that may make your life difficult if you're not expecting them. There is a wealth of information available on this subject in the <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-flexbox-1/#flex-items" target="_blank">flexbox working draft</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            This is part of flexbox, and is entirely expected. However, flexbox layout is not always appropriate so it's possible to add a <code>occlss-layout__cell</code> child element to your <code>occlss-layout__col occlss-layout__col--x</code> columns
            which defines an area of your column as <code>display: block</code> allowing you to lay out the contents of your layout elements like you would normally.
